---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const offers = [
  ['📚', 'Real courses, by topic', 'Dozens of courses across theology, philosophy, history, language, spirituality, music, the arts — and modern skills like AI.'],
  ['🎓', 'Taught from the sources', "Courses are drawn from the works of leading Sikh scholars and writers, each acting as the course's professor."],
  ['🧭', 'Guided learning paths', 'Ordered tracks take you from the basics to deeper study, so you always know what to learn next.'],
  ['📝', 'Tests & certificates', 'Each course ends with a test. Pass with 80%+ to unlock the next course and earn a printable certificate.'],
  ['♿', 'Open & accessible', 'Read-aloud, larger text, high-contrast mode, offline access — built so everyone can use it.'],
  ['🌍', 'Free, forever for now', 'Every course is free today. We may add paid offerings later, but open access stays at our core.'],
  ['🎓', 'Graduate seminars', '500-level advanced seminars across every subject — research-focused, scholarly, for serious students who want to go as deep as possible.'],
];
const steps = [
  ['Browse or follow a path.', 'Pick a topic, search the catalogue, or follow a guided learning path.'],
  ['Learn at your pace.', 'Work through lessons written in clear English, with key terms in Punjabi (Gurmukhi).'],
  ['Take notes & track progress.', 'Make notes as you go, build a streak, and earn badges on your dashboard.'],
  ['Pass the test, earn a certificate.', 'Score 80%+ to complete a course and unlock what comes next.'],
];
const stats = [
  { n: '531+', label: 'Courses' },
  { n: '23', label: 'Topics' },
  { n: '38+', label: 'Learning paths' },
  { n: '100%', label: 'Free' },
];
---
<Base title="About — Sikh University" description="Why Sikh University exists: a free, open space for anyone, anywhere to dig deeper into Sikhi and modern skills.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <header class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-brand to-navy-strong text-white">
    <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -right-24 -top-24 h-96 w-96 rounded-full bg-saffron/20 blur-3xl"></div>
    <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -left-12 bottom-0 h-64 w-64 rounded-full bg-blue/20 blur-3xl"></div>
    <div class="wrap relative py-20">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-saffron/40 bg-saffron/10 px-4 py-1.5 font-sans text-sm text-saffron mb-6">
        <span class="gur text-base">ਸਿੱਖ ਯੂਨੀਵਰਸਿਟੀ</span>
        <span class="text-white/50">·</span>
        <span>Free Open University</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="max-w-3xl text-4xl font-bold text-white sm:text-5xl leading-tight">A space to <span class="text-saffron">dig deeper</span><br class="hidden sm:block" /> into Sikhi.</h1>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-lg text-white/85 leading-relaxed">Sikh University is a free, open online university — built so that anyone, anywhere can study Sikhi seriously, from authentic sources, at their own pace.</p>
      <!-- Stats row -->
      <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 sm:flex sm:gap-8">
        {stats.map((s) => (
          <div class="text-center sm:text-left">
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-saffron">{s.n}</div>
            <div class="font-sans text-sm text-white/60">{s.label}</div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/catalog">Browse courses</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://sikharchive.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit Sikh Archive →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div aria-hidden="true" class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 h-20 bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent to-paper"></div>
  </header>

  <!-- Why we built it -->
  <section class="wrap py-14">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Why we created Sikh University</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p>Sikhi is deep. Its history spans five centuries, its scripture holds the voices of the Gurus, the Bhagats, the Bhatts and devoted Gursikhs, and its philosophy speaks to the biggest questions of life. Yet for most people there has never been one welcoming, structured place to learn it — to move from a first question to real understanding.</p>
        <p>We built Sikh University to be that place: a calm, organised home where a curious beginner and a serious student are equally welcome. No fees. No barriers. No sign-up needed to start learning. Just open, careful teaching — available to the whole world.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Offers -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-line">
    <div class="wrap py-14">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">What the university offers</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {offers.map((o) => (
          <div class="rounded-xl2 border border-line bg-paper p-5 transition-shadow hover:shadow-card">
            <div class="text-3xl">{o[0]}</div>
            <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-bold">{o[1]}</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-[0.92rem] text-muted leading-relaxed">{o[2]}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How it works -->
  <section class="wrap py-14">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">How it works</h2>
    <ol class="mt-6 space-y-4">
      {steps.map((s, i) => (
        <li class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-brand text-white text-sm font-bold">{i + 1}</span>
          <div class="pt-0.5">
            <span class="font-semibold text-navy">{s[0]}</span>{' '}
            <span class="text-muted">{s[1]}</span>
          </div>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ol>
  </section>

  <!-- Founder -->
  <section class="wrap pb-14">
    <div class="rounded-xl2 border border-line bg-surface overflow-hidden shadow-card">
      <!-- Top accent bar -->
      <div class="h-1.5 w-full bg-gradient-to-r from-saffron via-brand to-navy-strong"></div>
      <div class="p-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 items-start">
          <!-- Avatar circle -->
          <div class="shrink-0">
            <div class="relative">
              <div class="flex h-24 w-24 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-saffron to-brand text-white text-2xl font-bold shadow-lg ring-4 ring-saffron/20">
                JS
              </div>
              <div class="absolute -bottom-1 -right-1 h-7 w-7 rounded-full bg-ok flex items-center justify-center text-white text-xs">✓</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Content -->
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <div class="font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-muted mb-1">Founder</div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">Bhai Jasvant Singh <span class="gur">ਪੰਛੀ</span></h2>
            <div class="mt-1 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-full bg-saffron-soft px-3 py-1 font-sans text-xs font-semibold text-saffron-deep">Sikh Educator</span>
              <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-full bg-surface px-3 py-1 border border-line font-sans text-xs text-muted">Global Pracharik</span>
              <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-full bg-surface px-3 py-1 border border-line font-sans text-xs text-muted">Amrit Sanchar Lehar 2023–24</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">Sikh University was founded by <strong>Bhai Jasvant Singh ਪੰਛੀ</strong>, a Sikh educator and pracharik who has dedicated his life to sharing the knowledge of Guru Sahib with the world. In 2023–2024, Bhai Jasvant Singh led a global Amrit Sanchar lehar — a movement through which thousands of souls took Amrit and reconnected with the path of the Guru.</p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-muted max-w-3xl">He has traveled the world doing parchar for years, guided by one simple vision: that every person — regardless of background — deserves the opportunity to build their own personal, intimate relationship with God, and to become the best version of themselves.</p>
            <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-saffron bg-saffron-soft/40 px-4 py-3">
              <p class="text-sm italic text-navy">"Sikh University is an expression of that vision: free, open, and built for the world."</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Sikh Archive partnership -->
  <section class="wrap pb-14">
    <div class="rounded-xl2 border border-line bg-gradient-to-br from-brand/5 to-surface p-8">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
        <div class="text-4xl shrink-0">🗂️</div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Together with the Sikh Archive</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 max-w-2xl text-muted">Sikh University works alongside the <strong>Sikh Archive</strong> — a growing library of Sikh sources, history and free courses. Our courses point you there to read deeper, and the two sites are designed to work hand in hand.</p>
          <a class="btn mt-4" href="https://sikharchive.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit the Sikh Archive →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Accuracy -->
  <section class="wrap pb-14">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">A note on accuracy</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">Accuracy is sacred to us. Many courses are drafted with AI to make broad teaching possible quickly, and every one carries a clear <strong>"Created by AI"</strong> label. All content is reviewed for accuracy, Gurbani is handled with reverence, and we welcome corrections — please use the <a class="underline" href="/feedback">feedback page</a> to tell us anything we should fix.</p>
      <a class="btn btn-primary mt-6" href="/catalog">Start learning →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why we built this -->
  <section class="wrap pb-14">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Why we built Sikh University</h2>
      <p class="mt-1 font-sans text-sm text-saffron-deep uppercase tracking-widest"><span class="gur">ਸਿੱਖ</span> — the learner who never stops</p>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-[0.97rem] leading-relaxed text-muted">
        <p>The word <span class="gur">ਸਿੱਖ</span> literally means <em>learner</em> — one who sits at the feet of the Guru and never stops seeking. Gurbani's call to seek, to ask, to grow is not a suggestion; it is written into our very name. A Sikh is defined not by the knowledge they already have, but by their lifelong commitment to learning.</p>
        <p>But something is breaking. The writings of the Gurus and the great Gursikhs — penned in Punjabi, Braj Bhasha, Sant Bhasha, Persian, and Sanskrit — are becoming inaccessible to most of our global community. Children grow up in Toronto, London, Auckland, and São Paulo. They want to connect with <span class="gur">ਗੁਰੂ ਸਾਹਿਬ</span>. They want to read the <span class="gur">ਸ੍ਰੀ ਗੁਰੂ ਗਰੰਥ ਸਾਹਿਬ ਜੀ</span>. But the languages have changed, the scholars are hard to reach, and the gap between the Guru's wisdom and their daily life keeps growing.</p>
        <p>Languages drift. Generations lose threads. Community connections thin. But the longing for <span class="gur">ਵਾਹਿਗੁਰੂ</span> does not disappear — it just goes unanswered.</p>
        <p>Sikh University was built to answer that longing. Every course here is a bridge — from the depth of the Guru Sahib's writings to the heart of a Sikh alive today. The medium is English. The sources are authentic. The scholars are real. And the destination is always the same: your own, personal, unbreakable bond with <span class="gur">ਵਾਹਿਗੁਰੂ</span>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Sacred Content Disclaimer -->
  <section class="wrap pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl rounded-xl2 border border-line bg-surface p-6 shadow-card">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Sacred content &amp; disclaimer</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-[0.97rem] leading-relaxed text-muted">
        <p>Sikh University is an independent educational resource. It is not a religious authority, and it is not affiliated with, sponsored by, or endorsed by the Shiromani Gurdwara Parbandhak Committee (SGPC), the Akal Takht, any Takht, any Gurdwara, or any other Sikh institution.</p>
        <p>Our content — especially material drafted with the help of AI — is provided for learning and may contain errors. It is not a substitute for guidance from the <span class="gur">ਸ੍ਰੀ ਗੁਰੂ ਗਰੰਥ ਸਾਹਿਬ ਜੀ</span>, the <span class="gur">ਪੰਜ ਪਿਆਰੇ</span>, Granthis, or qualified scholars. For matters of faith, practice, or doctrine, please turn to authentic sources and your local <span class="gur">ਸੰਗਤ</span>.</p>
        <p>Gurbani is presented with reverence and to the best of our ability for accuracy; even so, we encourage you to verify it against authentic, authoritative sources. The platform makes no warranty as to the completeness or accuracy of any content and is not liable for any reliance placed on it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
